DateReviewed: 2026-02-02
Description: Our article today will do a comparison of a number of Kubernetes DB operators. After a bit of background, we dive in, first by going through the types of operators. They divide them into proprietary vendor-specific ones, community open source, and finally enterprise grade open source ones. They then show us a chart with various features, so we can see what they do (and don't do). Next up they do a bit of analysis on what matters on the biz outcomes side. First is cost efficiency (that compounds), second resilience you can depend on, third is scalability without complexity, and finally governance and compliance made simpler. Each of these has a para explaining what they are and how they fit the general picture. From here, the article wanders off into being a bit of a PR piece, promoting Percona operators, which is fair enough. Good background and explainations.
BottomLine: Decent comparison of various DB operators
